The paper focuses on privacy-preserving machine learning, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and graphics processing units (GPUs) suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The optimization techniques used in the paper may also suggest a connection to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
